Here is the handler code for a slider in XCode 7
@IBAction func handleSlider(sender: UISlider) { var value = sender.value print(&quot;value \(value) &quot;) }  If you type in this code, XCode will issue the following warning near the declaration of the var value, Variable ‘value’ was never mutated; consider changing to ‘let’ constant. Once you choose that option, the code changes to this and the warning disappears.
@IBAction func handleSlider(sender: UISlider) { let value = sender.
